metadata.description: Power Report Frequency. Choose how often you want your RGBW Dimmer to report power consumption (W) to your controller. NOTE: must be 0, or an increment of 30. Default: 3600
metadata.label: Power Report Frequency

metadata.description: Energy Report Threshold. Choose how you want your RGBW Dimmer to report energy use (kWh) to your hub. The number entered as value corresponds to decimal values in energy useage change. So if 10 is entered by default, the RGBW Dimmer will report any change in energy use over 0.1 kWh. Energy reports are sent in t least 30-second intervals.
metadata.label: Energy Report Threshold

metadata.description: Energy Report Frequency. Choose how often you want your RGBW Dimmer to report energy (kWh) to your controller. NOTE: must be 0, or an increment of 30. Default: 3600
metadata.label: Energy Report Frequency

metadata.description: RGBW/HSB Wall Switch Mode. Choose how switches connected to the input terminals control your LED strip. In the default RGBW mode, each switch connected to each input terminal controls the RGBW chnnels separately (so IN1 for red, IN2 for green, etc.) with a single click for ON/OFF, double click to full brightness, and press-and-hold to dim (momentary switches only). In the HSB, IN1 controls hue, IN2 - saturation, IN3 - brightness, IN4 - white with single click for last set value or value 0, double click to max value, and press-and-hold to set custom value. Default: RGBW mode
metadata.label: RGBW/HSB Wall Switch Mode

metadata.description: Ramp Rate (switch). Adjust the ramp rate for your RGBW dimmer (fade-in/fade-out effect for on/off operation). Values correspond to the number of seconds it takes for the dimmer to reach full brightness or turn off when operated from the connected wall switch. Note that 0 is instant on/off. Default : 3 seconds
metadata.label: Ramp Rate (switch)

metadata.description: Ramp Rate (Z-Wave). Adjust the ramp rate for your RGBW dimmer (fade-in/fade-out effect for on/off operation). Values correspond to the number of seconds it takes for the dimmer to reach full brightness or turn off when operated remotely from the Z-Wave hub Note that 0 is instant on/off. Default : 3 seconds
metadata.label: Ramp Rate (Z-Wave)
